project.name: Bulldozer domain v1
project.description:
Simple Vehicle domain where a person has to get in to a vehicle, drive it somewhere, get out, and return to some other location. Recursion is a problem in this domain because the roads and bridges go both directions.
This is a stantard planning domain originally developed as part of the UPCPOP release from Barret, Christianson, Friedman, Golden, Penberthy, Sun and Weld, 1996.

action.precondition: from.road->exists(x:Place| x = to) and thing.at = from and thing.mobile = true and from <> to
from.bridge->exists(x:Place| x = to) and thing.at = from and thing.mobile = true and from <> to
person.at = place and person.mobile = true and vehicle.at = place
action.postcondition: person.driving = vehicle and vehicle.mobile = true and person.at = null and person.mobile = false

action.precondition: person.driving = vehicle and vehicle.at = place and vehicle.mobile = true
action.postcondition: person.at = place and person.mobile = true and person.driving = null and vehicle.mobile = false
